{
  "_comment": "Multilingual brochure label ledger for extract_pdf.py / extract_pptx.py. Each canonical field lists label aliases across European languages; the extractor appends these to its English baseline (English stays the in-code default, so CEE decks are unaffected) and a page is treated as a property page when >=2 of these match, in ANY language. 'kind' matches the parser: text | num | rent. Labels are matched on their own line (spec-sheet style); a deck with NO own-line labels on any page falls back to same-line 'Label value' parsing (extract_pdf._apply_inline_labels), so these aliases serve both layouts - only image/vector-only decks then need the vision fallback. Extend freely per new market and record it in reference/memory.md.",
