    "_comment_ld": "developer = the party that BUILT/is building (developer/promoter); landlord = the party that OWNS/lets an existing building (owner/landlord/freeholder/asset-manager). Owner-language terms (Eigentümer, Propietario, Propriétaire, Eigenaar, Proprietario, Proprietário, Właściciel, etc.) live in `landlord`, NOT `developer` - an owner is never a developer. The English compounds 'Owner/developer' stay in `developer` (they explicitly carry 'developer'); a bare owner word never backfills developer downstream.",
